Top Stories (January 10)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR SAYS PROGRESS WAS MADE IN CALIFORNIA POWER TALKS
After meeting behind closed doors for seven hours, government officials said 
progress was made during a White House-brokered meeting to identify solutions 
for California's troubled electricity market.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/10/eng-djn/eng-djn_112027_38_9608982484788

PG&E SAYS ITS CURRENTLY UNABLE TO BORROW MORE MONEY
PG&E Corp.'s (PCG) Pacific Gas & Electric Co. said the disparity between 
wholesale power prices and the current utility rates has made further 
borrowing impossible, according to a Form 8-K filed Wednesday with the 
Securities and Exchange Commission.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/10/eng-djn/eng-djn_160035_224_442865708843

JUSTICE DEPARTMENT OK'S ARKANSAS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE RETAIL JOINT VENTURE
The Arkansas Electric Cooperative Corp., has obtained Justice Department 
approval to jointly market electric power to retail customers when Arkansas 
moves to deregulate its electric market.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/10/eng-djn/eng-djn_184026_22_6107542845421

MASSACHUSETTS ATTORNEY GENERAL WANTS ELECTRIC TRANSMISSION CAPACITY ADDED
Massachusetts Attorney General Thomas F. Reilly yesterday urged electric grid 
managers to step up efforts to add new transmission capacity in the state and 
region to help curb soaring electric costs.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/10/krtbn/0000-0176-GL-ELECTRIC

-IS NUCLEAR ENERGY ON THE VERGE OF A RESURGENCE? - ISSUEALERT FOR JANUARY 10, 
2001
According to the Nuclear Energy Institute, for the first time in more than a 
decade, production costs (outlays for fuel and operations and maintenance) at 
U.S. nuclear plants are the lowest of any major reliable electricity source, 
dropping below coal-fired power plants.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/writersd
esk/2001/01/10/eng-powerm-000001/eng-powerm-000001_125702_201_045852864627

